body:
## Environment
- OS: Windows 11 Pro
- claude-mem: 13.10.2
- Bun: 1.3.14, installed via official installer (`npx claude-mem install`) — this creates `bun.exe` only, no `bun.cmd`
- Claude Code: 2.1.207

## Symptom
Every hook fails on startup:
```
SessionStart:startup hook error
Failed with non-blocking status code: ""bun"" non è riconosciuto come comando interno o esterno,
```
(Italian locale; translates to `""bun"" is not recognized as an internal or external command`.)

`where.exe bun` correctly resolves to `C:\Users\<user>\.bun\bin\bun.exe`, and `bun --version` works fine everywhere else — so this is not a PATH problem.

## Root cause

In `scripts/bun-runner.js`, `findBun()`:

```js
if (pathCheck.status === 0 && pathCheck.stdout.trim()) {
  if (IS_WINDOWS) {
    const bunCmdPath = pathCheck.stdout.split('\n').find(line => line.trim().endsWith('bun.cmd'));
    if (bunCmdPath) {
      return bunCmdPath.trim();
    }
  }
  return 'bun';   // <-- reached when only bun.exe is present
}
```

When `where bun` succeeds but only returns a `bun.exe` path (official installer, no npm shim), the function falls through to `return 'bun'` — the bare command name, not a resolved path.

That bare string then hits the Windows spawn block further down:

```js
if (IS_WINDOWS) {
  const quote = (s) => `"${String(s).replace(/"/g, '\\"')}"`;
  spawnOptions.shell = true;
  spawnCmd = [bunPath, ...args].map(quote).join(' ');
  spawnArgs = [];
}
```

`bunPath = 'bun'` gets quoted to `"bun"` and joined into a single shell string executed via `shell:true` → `cmd.exe`. With an unresolved bare command name in this position, cmd.exe receives a malformed token and reports it back doubly-quoted (`""bun""`), failing every hook (`SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `PostToolUse`, `Stop`).

Confirmed this is specific to the resolved value, not the spawn mechanism itself:
```js
// Works fine when passed a plain string directly (not through findBun's bare fallback):
spawnSync('cmd', ['/c', 'bun', '--version'], {encoding:'utf8'})
// → status 0, stdout: 1.3.14
```

## Relation to #2528

#2528 (closed, `not planned`) proposed preferring `bun.exe` over `bun.cmd` in `findBun()` for exactly this reason (AV/EPERM angle there, but the same root fix). Looking at current `main`, that preference was only ever applied to the **hardcoded fallback path list** (`bunPaths`, further down — which already correctly resolves `~/.bun/bin/bun.exe`), not to the **`where bun` branch** shown above. Users whose `where bun` succeeds (i.e. Bun is on PATH — the common/recommended case) never reach the hardcoded fallback, so they hit the bare-`'bun'` bug regardless of #2528's fix existing elsewhere in the file.

## Fix (verified locally)

```diff
   if (pathCheck.status === 0 && pathCheck.stdout.trim()) {
     if (IS_WINDOWS) {
-      const bunCmdPath = pathCheck.stdout.split('\n').find(line => line.trim().endsWith('bun.cmd'));
+      const lines = pathCheck.stdout.split('\n');
+      const bunExePath = lines.find(line => line.trim().toLowerCase().endsWith('bun.exe'));
+      if (bunExePath) {
+        return bunExePath.trim();
+      }
+      const bunCmdPath = lines.find(line => line.trim().endsWith('bun.cmd'));
       if (bunCmdPath) {
         return bunCmdPath.trim();
       }
     }
     return 'bun';
   }
```

Applied to both `plugins/marketplaces/thedotmack/plugin/scripts/bun-runner.js` and the corresponding versioned copy in `plugins/cache/thedotmack/claude-mem/<version>/scripts/bun-runner.js` — worker starts correctly afterward, all hooks succeed.

Happy to open a PR with this change if useful.

## Related
- #2528 (proposed the same `.exe`-first preference, closed not planned — appears never merged for this code path)
- #1452, #2150, #2186 (related Windows bun-spawn issues, different symptoms/fixes)
